      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RUINATION (8) was an impressive winner in the quickest time of the program two back then hit the frame when third at this track (17.89) last time. Can find winning form. FUMBLES (7) is a capable type and proved too classy last time to win by 1.3 lengths at this track in a handy 17.72 beating Mepunga Shine. Solid beginner and with a good start should have clear running out wide. Hard to fault his form and he makes plenty of appeal. JAKE PERALTA (1) produced a modest effort most recently when seventh at Maitland over 400m behind My Moon Shadow (23.27) in a Mix 2/3. Was in the money prior to that. Has performed well from this box with a win and three minor placings to his name from eight starts. Should be about the money. STILL AVAILABLE (2) is not to be discarded.",
